  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nI recently try the Kubernetes extension to generates Kubernetes ressources and I have some feedback / enhacement proposals : \r\n\r\n- When specifing container ressources, there is a log that seems not necessary\r\n```\r\nApply requests cpu to:test-kubernetes\r\n```\r\n- The Ingress is using port value instead of port name, the deployment specify a port name of `http`, it would be better to use it instead of the port value.\r\n- When adding Smallrye Health, probes are added to the container spec with the following settings:\r\n```yaml\r\n            initialDelaySeconds: 0\r\n            periodSeconds: 30\r\n            successThreshold: 1\r\n```\r\nAs `initialDelaySeconds` is at 0, the first probe will always fails, and as `periodSeconds` is at 30s this means te container will be detected as RUNNING after 30s which is a lot for a typical Quarkus application that can starts in less than 3s even in constrainted environments. I'll suggest configuring  `initialDelaySeconds` to 3s or 5s.\r\nI also wonder why the periodSeconds has been set to 30s when the default is 10s.\r\n- There is no functionality to generates an HorizontalPodAutoscaling, using HPA in deployments is very common, this would be a great addition if Quarkus would be able to generate one.\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\n_No response_",
